description.narrative:
The main duties relate to support communication and outreach planning and implementation under the FAO Umbrella Programme for the Promotion and Application of the SSF Guidelines, in close consultation with members of the FAO Technical Network on Small-Scale Fisheries. This includes the following main responsibilities: 
?	Monitoring and analysis of technical, social, economic, environmental, institutional, and technology materials and developments within FAO at HQ and field levels and beyond (e.g. United Nations, intergovernmental, think-tank, academia, corporate and NGO/CSO reports) to keep abreast of relevant strategic developments and to ensure that they are consistently and accurately reflected in communications for FAO?s activities the context of the implementation of the SSF Guidelines;
?	Production of a variety of input for communication-related documents (brochures, guiding documents, newsletter, statements, briefings, talking points, key messages and other written communications) and web content to support the implementation of the SSF Guidelines, ensuring a high level of consistency and accuracy for a wide variety of audiences;
?	Collaboration in the development of improved/updated tools, systems, processes, and databases to improve internal and external communication in the context of the implementation of the SSF Guidelines; 
?	Participation in relevant multi-disciplinary teams, collaboration and engagement with other departments and external partners and support of the promotion of good practices; 
?	Promotion of knowledge sharing and information about securing sustainable small-scale fisheries, including at national, regional and international meetings and conferences; 
?	Assurance that communications produced adhere to corporate policy, in consultation with relevant departments and units, and provides analysis and recommendations as required; 
?	Preparation and organization of events and meetings; 
?	Facilitation of the sharing and dissemination of communication and knowledge products; 
?	Support to the FAO Technical Network on Small-Scale Fisheries (e.g. setting up of meetings, reporting, maintenance of shared documentation, etc.). 
The expected key achievement is to contribute to the development and strengthening of the communication and outreach activities of the Organization in the context of the implementation of the SSF Guidelines.
